This paper is about natural language generation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a framework for evaluating both diversity and quality of generated text, which involves combining human and statistical evaluation. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses techniques for improving the quality of generated text, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the techniques involve image captioning or video description.
